title: Chicago -- Live In Japan
description:
From waaaaaaay back in the early 1970s, one of the few live albums that Chicago released.  Most of the others are the one bootlegged concert from a gig in Montreal in 1969 -- there are like 5000 copies of it sold by different companies.  I bought thirty copies or so over the years just because I liked the packaging but then I gave up.

This is a great album, not as good as another, non-Chicago live album I&#039;ll be uploading soon, which is one of the greatest of all time....but much harder to get....


This album contains:


Dialogue (Parts I & II)

A Hit By Varese

Lowdown (Japanese version)

State of the Union

Saturday in the Park

Make Me Smile

So Much to Say, So Much to Give

Anxiety&#039;s Moment

West Virginia Fantasies

Colour My World

To Be Free

Now More than Ever

Beginnings

Mississippi Delta City Blues

A Song For Richard and His Friend

Does Anybody Really Know What Time It Is? (Free-form intro)

Does Anybody Really Know What Time It Is?

Questions 67 & 68 (Japanese Version)

25 or 6 to 4

I&#039;m a Man


Enjoy!
